info.title: Vocera AI API
info.description: Complete API documentation for Vocera AI Platform. This API provides endpoints for managing AI-powered conversations, call analytics, and quality monitoring features.

get.description: Retrieve a list of all available enumeration values used throughout the API

get.description: Retrieve a paginated list of call logs with detailed filtering options

parameters.name: call_ended_reason__in
parameters.description: Filter calls by one or more end reasons (comma-separated). Example: 'HANGUP,TRANSFER'

parameters.name: call_ended_reason__icontains
parameters.description: Filter calls where end reason contains the specified text (case-insensitive)

parameters.name: timestamp__gte
parameters.description: Filter calls after or equal to this timestamp (ISO 8601 format)

parameters.name: timestamp__lte
parameters.description: Filter calls before or equal to this timestamp (ISO 8601 format)

parameters.name: duration__gte
parameters.description: Filter calls with duration greater than or equal to specified seconds

parameters.name: duration__lte
parameters.description: Filter calls with duration less than or equal to specified seconds

200.description: Successfully retrieved paginated list of call logs

count.description: Total number of call logs matching the filter criteria

next.description: URL to fetch the next page of results, null if this is the last page

previous.description: URL to fetch the previous page of results, null if this is the first page

results.description: List of call log entries for the current page

post.description: Create a new call log entry with detailed information about a conversation

requestBody.description: Call log details to be created

401.description: Authentication credentials were not provided or are invalid

voice_recording.description: Audio file of the call recording. Either voice_recording or voice_recording_url must be provided

voice_recording_url.description: URL to the call recording audio file. Either voice_recording or voice_recording_url must be provided

customer_number.description: Optional phone number of the customer

transcript_json.description: JSON object containing the transcript of the call. Can be in Vocera, Vapi, Retell or Deepgram format

get.description: Retrieve a list of test results with filtering options

parameters.name: agent
parameters.description: Filter results by specific agent ID

parameters.name: status
parameters.description: Filter results by their current status (e.g., completed, pending)

parameters.name: created_after
parameters.description: Filter results created after this timestamp (ISO 8601 format)

200.description: Successfully retrieved list of test results

get.description: Get details of a specific test result

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: ID of the test result to retrieve

CallLogDetail.description: Detailed information about a single conversation or call

duration.description: Duration of the call in seconds

call_ended_reason.description: Reason why the call ended (e.g., HANGUP, TRANSFER)

metrics.description: Various metrics collected during the call

agent.description: ID of the agent this metric is associated with

eval_type.title: Evaluation Type
eval_type.description: Type of evaluation for this metric. Determines how the metric is scored and displayed
